other_tests.findings: Normal liver, spleen, gallbladder, pancreas, and adrenals. Kidneys demonstrate symmetric contrast enhancement with incidental note made of extrarenal pelvises bilaterally. Fat-containing lesion within the right upper pole likely represents an angiomyolipoma. Lap band is in standard configuration, stomach is decompressed, and lap band injection port is normal. Visualized loops of small bowel are normal. Pelvic organs are normal in appearance. Bladder is unremarkable, note of bilateral tubal occlusion devices, and 2.0-cm left adnexal cyst. Colon and appendix are unremarkable.
